\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces The closure-certified deduction sub-module of a text-to-logic pipeline. A high-recall disjunctive LLM reader emits a sound relation set per span; an exact composition table and forward closure narrow the held-out query edge; the system emits a singleton, abstains on a residual disjunction, or---the load-bearing case---abstains with `no relation' when no derivation path reaches the query. A confidence threshold cannot separate confident-present from confident-absent answers; the structural no-derivation certificate can.}}{3}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:fig1}{{1}{3}{The closure-certified deduction sub-module of a text-to-logic pipeline. A high-recall disjunctive LLM reader emits a sound relation set per span; an exact composition table and forward closure narrow the held-out query edge; the system emits a singleton, abstains on a residual disjunction, or---the load-bearing case---abstains with `no relation' when no derivation path reaches the query. A confidence threshold cannot separate confident-present from confident-absent answers; the structural no-derivation certificate can}{figure.1}{}}
